word: I do not want to seem
parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: A prolonged form of a primary verb, doko dok'-o of the same meaning; to think; by implication, to seem.
Probably adverb of comparative from hos; which how, i.e. In that manner.
To frighten away, terrify. From ek and phobeo; to frighten utterly.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
A primary preposition denoting the channel of an act; through.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A letter, dispatch, epistle, message. From epistello; a written message.
